Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

On Saturday 11 April, Spirit Airlines and WestJet will each be running a special flight departing from Panama City.
Spirit Airlines
Spirit Airlines will be running a special flight departing from Panama City, Tocumen International Airport, to Fort Lauderdale, Florida, USA (Flight NK 6501). There are a limited number of seats and the date and time of departure may change. You must have a valid ESTA to travel on this flight. Passengers with a current ESTA are qualified for this flight as long as they have been away from UK/EU or China for 14 days. Please note that no new ESTA applications are being processed at this time.
You can book this flight on the Spirit website
There are onward flights to London-Heathrow Airport from Miami International Airport, you should coordinate your onward connection to the UK accordingly.
WestJet
WestJet will be running a special flight departing from Panama City, Tocumen International Airport to Toronto, Canada (Flight WS3909). There are a limited number of seats. Passengers are required to have a valid Electronic Travel Authorisation (ETA) and a confirmed onward flight to the UK departing within 24hrs of arrival in Toronto. This might include an overnight stay at the Toronto Pearson Airport but transit to a second Canadian City is not permitted.
Seats for this flight are allocated at the time of booking on the WestJet website.
If you choose to book with WestJet, please send us your booking confirmation to ensure we can assist with advice for your transit in Canada.
We are not aware of any future international flights from Panama City after this date, until the flight suspensions are lifted. Please act fast if you wish to use this opportunity to leave Panama.
You are responsible for coordinating travel to the airport. Transportation is restricted and you may have to book a private driver or taxi. We can facilitate a letter in Spanish and English for the driver that may assist with checkpoints to and from airport. Please email us your flight confirmation along with the following details: the driver’s full name; identification number (cedula), license plate number and make and model of the vehicle, and the names of British Nationals travelling with you at BEPanama.CV@fco.gov.uk.
If local authorities need confirmation that you are in transit to the airport, call +507-297-6550 for assistance.
What to do
If you cannot leave Panama at this time, you should:
email your details to BEPanama.CV@fco.gov.uk, so we can alert you when options become available
follow the advice of local authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus
find accommodation that’s suitable for your needs
keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well
Future travel options
There are currently no further commercial options available to return to the UK from Panama. All other commercial flights have ceased operation to/from Panama until at least 22 April 2020.
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy on +507 297-6550 or through the recommended consular contacts.
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately
